{"repo": "THUDM/slime", "pull_number": 1238, "instance_id": "THUDM__slime-1238", "issue_numbers": [1236], "base_commit": "3d7599aa4d3a9b9114e4b68724b2591620684d50", "patch": "diff --git a/build_conda.sh b/build_conda.sh\nindex a1d19543dd..3baf42ed42 100644\n--- a/build_conda.sh\n+++ b/build_conda.sh\n@@ -46,10 +46,6 @@ NVCC_APPEND_FLAGS=\"--threads 4\" \\\n   --no-build-isolation \\\n   --config-settings \"--build-option=--cpp_ext --cuda_ext --parallel 8\" git+https://github.com/NVIDIA/apex.git@10417aceddd7d5d05d7cbf7b0fc2daad1105f8b4\n \n-git clone https://github.com/NVIDIA/Megatron-LM.git --recursive && \\\n-    cd Megatron-LM && git checkout ${MEGATRON_COMMIT} && \\\n-    pip install -e .\n-\n pip install git+https://github.com/fzyzcjy/torch_memory_saver.git@dc6876905830430b5054325fa4211ff302169c6b --no-cache-dir --force-reinstall\n pip install git+https://github.com/fzyzcjy/Megatron-Bridge.git@dev_rl --no-build-isolation\n pip install nvidia-modelopt[torch]>=0.37.0 --no-build-isolation\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[Bug] Duplicate Megatron-LM installation in build_conda.sh\n ## Description\n\n  The `build_conda.sh` script contains duplicate Megatron-LM cloning and installation steps, which causes unnecessary redundancy and incorrect directory structure during the build process.\n\n  ## Current Behavior\n\n  The script clones and installs Megatron-LM **twice**:\n\n  1. **First installation** (lines 49-51):\n     ```bash\n     git clone https://github.com/NVIDIA/Megatron-LM.git --recursive && \\\n         cd Megatron-LM && git checkout ${MEGATRON_COMMIT} && \\\n         pip install -e .\n  - Location: $BASE_DIR/sglang/Megatron-LM (incorrect, since the script is still in the sglang directory from line 29)\n  - Uses undefined variable ${MEGATRON_COMMIT} (not set anywhere in the script)\n\n  2. **Second installation** (lines 58-61):\n  cd $BASE_DIR\n  git clone https://github.com/NVIDIA/Megatron-LM.git --recursive && \\\n    cd Megatron-LM/ && git checkout core_v0.14.0 && \\\n    pip install -e .\n    - Location: $BASE_DIR/Megatron-LM (correct)\n    - Explicitly uses core_v0.14.0 version\n\n  The patch application at line 84 uses $BASE_DIR/Megatron-LM, which relies on the second installation.\n\n  ## Expected Behavior\n\n  Megatron-LM should be cloned and installed only once at the correct location with the proper version specified.\n\n  Comparison with Dockerfile\n\n  The docker/Dockerfile handles this correctly:\n  - Defines MEGATRON_COMMIT as an ARG (line 7)\n  - Clones Megatron-LM only once (lines 52-54)\n  - Has proper error handling for patch application\n\n\n\n\n\n<img width=\"2160\" height=\"984\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/558c864f-62eb-4aff-9fdb-349e216c5b53\" />\n\n\n\nI'm uncertain about this. If this counts as a bug, I will fix it and submit a pull request.\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/THUDM/slime/commit/4ebcbfc9d86d75b387c5c684b60f3eed186d2886"], "created_at": "2025-12-28T15:56:39Z"}
{"repo": "THUDM/slime", "pull_number": 1354, "instance_id": "THUDM__slime-1354", "issue_numbers": [1341], "base_commit": "34b38ec67817d55284bf7b626948ca1e6cc18742", "patch": "diff --git a/slime/backends/fsdp_utils/__init__.py b/slime/backends/fsdp_utils/__init__.py\nindex 05099e93c0..444b43089d 100644\n--- a/slime/backends/fsdp_utils/__init__.py\n+++ b/slime/backends/fsdp_utils/__init__.py\n@@ -1,13 +1,8 @@\n import logging\n \n-\n try:\n-    _TORCH_MEMORY_SAVER_AVAILABLE = True\n-except ImportError:\n-    logging.warning(\"torch_memory_saver is not installed, refer to : https://github.com/fzyzcjy/torch_memory_saver\")\n-    _TORCH_MEMORY_SAVER_AVAILABLE = False\n+    from torch.distributed.fsdp import fully_shard  # noqa: F401\n \n-try:\n     _FSDP_AVAILABLE = True\n except ImportError as e:\n     logging.warning(f\"FSDP backend dependencies not available: {e}\")\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Meaningless import check logic\nhttps://github.com/THUDM/slime/blob/0ab41513ff231795bd9aa743fdcc1758c43d46e0/slime/backends/fsdp_utils/__init__.py#L4-L14\n\nI wonder the purpose of the quoted code and where the import actually gets checked.\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Nice catch. Fixed in https://github.com/THUDM/slime/pull/1354\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/THUDM/slime/commit/73098f2e6b2a22935535edaab7273a15d763a628", "https://github.com/THUDM/slime/commit/7cfe09fd828793658ec77461cbf0379eebc329d8"], "created_at": "2026-01-07T10:35:01Z"}
{"repo": "THUDM/slime", "pull_number": 1372, "instance_id": "THUDM__slime-1372", "issue_numbers": [1370], "base_commit": "60bfe04fee2c434dbea46bb2512db2a77a0a312d", "patch": "diff --git a/slime/utils/ppo_utils.py b/slime/utils/ppo_utils.py\nindex f89199227b..f10a8c8837 100644\n--- a/slime/utils/ppo_utils.py\n+++ b/slime/utils/ppo_utils.py\n@@ -253,9 +253,10 @@ def get_reinforce_plus_plus_returns(\n             full_kl_response = local_kl_chunk\n \n         # Step 3: Compute returns on full response kl tensor.\n-        token_level_rewards = -kl_coef * full_kl_response\n         full_mask = loss_masks[i]\n         assert full_mask.sum().item() > 0, f\"Sequence at index {i} is fully masked.\"\n+        masked_kl = full_kl_response * full_mask\n+        token_level_rewards = -kl_coef * masked_kl\n         last_idx = full_mask.nonzero(as_tuple=True)[0][-1]\n         token_level_rewards[last_idx] += rewards[i]\n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "\u3010BUG\u3011no masking for tool_response in token_level_rewards when applied to agentic rl\nIn slime/utils/ppo_utils.py def get_reinforce_plus_plus_returns(...)\n\nwhen **calculating 'returns_for_seq' with 'token_level_rewards', no mask is applied to the kl w.r.t. tool_response**, this may be problematic when applied to agentic rl, because tool_response is returned by the environment, and should not engage in the forward computation. Otherwise, all kl of tool_response may accumulate when calculating the return.\n\nDo I understand it correctly?\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "we will always mask the tool response with loss mask when calculating loss or doing logging, so calculating kl here won't harm.\n> we will always mask the tool response with loss mask when calculating loss or doing logging, so calculating kl here won't harm.\n\nbut the kl of tool response will be propagted to all its former tokens by the following operation?\n\nrunning_return = token_level_rewards[t] + gamma * running_return\nreturns_for_seq[t] = running_return\noh, sorry I was wrong, thank you for the fix!\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/THUDM/slime/commit/5bd54f346f873ed5be033d3180d2956a7dcb538a", "https://github.com/THUDM/slime/commit/e8728f939dd984535f1a8e8dae39051583e5e0c7"], "created_at": "2026-01-09T09:19:22Z"}
